{{Quote|I'm glad to hear there's some [[Daredevil|new blood]] running around out there. [[Avengers|Heroes]] and their [[Battle of New York|consequences]] are why we have our current opportunities.|Leland Owlsley|Into the Ring}}
'''Leland Owlsley''' was a ruthless financier and associate of [[Wilson Fisk]] who played a part in Fisk's crusade to rebuild [[Hell's Kitchen]], controlling Fisk's money flow and ensuring that his large profits were almost impossible to trace. He eventually lost faith in Fisk's leadership and attempted to assassinate Fisk's lover [[Vanessa Marianna]] in order to refocus him. When Fisk learned of this, he got revenge by [[Murder of Leland Owlsley|killing]] him.

==Biography==
{{MD|Leland Owlsley (Earth-199999)}}
===Early Life===
====Criminal Money Man====
{{Quote|I've spent my entire life hiding assets overseas from pricks like you.|Leland Owlsley to [[Wilson Fisk]]|Rabbit in a Snowstorm (episode)}}
Leland Owlsley spent his career ensuring that his rich partner's cash transactions became almost impossible to track, thereby hiding any illegal action they might be involved with. As this line of work often involved criminal activity, Owlsley made sure to keep a portion of the money for himself and his [[Lee Owlsley|son]] in case they ever needed to go on the run from one of his partners.{{Ref|DD113}}

===Working with Wilson Fisk===
====Complications in New York====
[[File:Leland-Owlsley-Typing.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley working for [[Wilson Fisk]]]]
{{Quote|Again, I have to ask, why do we care? Every time one of [[Avengers|these guys]] punches someone through a building, our margins go up 3%. We should be celebrating."<br>"This is different. My [[Wilson Fisk|employer]] will be... displeased. We're being inconvenienced by a [[Daredevil|lone vigilante]].|Leland Owlsley and [[James Wesley]]|Into the Ring}}
Owlsley was recruited by [[Wilson Fisk]] to control his money inputs and outputs, ensuring the authorities could not uncover their work. Owlsley took great pride in his work, having years of experience working for high-ranking criminal organizations and keeping their investments safe and secure. Although he had great respect for Fisk, Owlsley never fully trusted him and ensured he had backup plans ready in case Fisk ever betrayed him.
[[File:Leland-Owlsley-Wesley-S1E1.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley has a meeting with [[James Wesley]]]]
One night, Owlsley waited on the top of a building, along with [[Madame Gao]], [[Nobu Yoshioka]], [[Anatoly Ranskahov]], and [[Vladimir Ranskahov]], awaiting the arrival of Fisk. Owlsley spent much of the time complaining about the cold weather and Gao's and Yoshioka's refusal to speak English. Eventually, [[James Wesley]] arrived, claiming Fisk was too busy to attend. Wesley began to question why the Ranskahov's supply was down, to which they claimed their shipment had been attacked by a [[Daredevil|masked vigilante]]. Owlsley remained unphased by the news, claiming that new heroes in the city meant more career opportunities for them in the aftermath.{{Ref|DD101}}
[[File:Wesley-Owlsley-Limo.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley speaking to [[James Wesley]]]]
A few days later, Owlsley met with [[James Wesley]] to discuss the recent trial of [[John Healy]]. Owlsley could not understand why Wesley had chosen to hire [[Nelson and Murdock]] rather than using his own lawyers; Wesley explained that the two lawyers were clean, unlike Owlsley's lawyers. Owlsley continued asking questions, wanting to know why Fisk did not just have Healy killed like all their other problems. When Owlsley wondered why [[Wilson Fisk]] was not there to explain this himself, Wesley told him Fisk was busy looking at art, which greatly annoyed Owlsley.{{Ref|DD103}}

====War with the Russians====
[[File:Leland-Owlsley-disgusted-look.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley sees blood on [[Wilson Fisk]]'s car]]
{{Quote|[[Daredevil|Masked vigilantes]], crazy [[Russian Mafia|Russians]]. I'm getting my stun gun out of storage.|Leland Owlsley|World on Fire}}
Owlsley was later called for another meeting, this time without the Ranskahov brothers. He observed pints of blood being washed off Fisk's car; when he asked if anyone else was concerned about the site, all he received was a laugh from [[Madame Gao]]. They were interrupted by the arrival of Wesley and [[Wilson Fisk]]. When Owlsley asked where the Ranskahov's were, Fisk announced that the [[Russian Mafia]] were no longer a part of their organization since Fisk had [[Murder of Anatoly Ranskahov|removed]] [[Anatoly Ranskahov]]'s head with his car door the night before.
[[File:Leland-Owlsley-Questions-Wilson-Fisk.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley questions [[Wilson Fisk]]'s statements]]
Both Gao and [[Nobu Yoshioka]] made it clear they were unhappy to have not been consulted in the matter; Owlsley also agreed. Fisk told Gao to continue moving her heroin to the Russians as usual until such a time that Fisk to take over the responsibility. Owlsley pointed out that the Russians' share of the money would likely go to Fisk, but Fisk promised all profits would be divided up equally between them. The group agreed on the proposal, with Owlsley noting he would not be foolish enough to go against them. Before they all departed, Owlsley nervously told them he would be collecting his stun gun.{{Ref|DD105}}

====Face to Face with the Masked Man====
[[File:Owlsley-Nobu.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley speaks to [[Nobu Yoshioka]]]]
{{Quote|The numbers are like tea leaves. Nobody reads them like I can.|Leland Owlsley to [[Nobu Yoshioka]]|Stick (episode)}}
Owlsley met with [[Nobu Yoshioka]] in a car park to discuss the transport of his [[Black Sky|cargo]], Owlsley made it clear that he knew what was being transported as he had decrypted the paperwork, he suggested that he and Yoshioka work to protect each other in light of the [[Bombing of Hell's Kitchen]] with the [[Russian Mafia]]. Yoshioka instead told him that all men must stand alone or fall, he then left leaving Owlsley confused by what he meant. Once Yoshioka had gone Owlsley made his way to his car alone.
[[File:Daredevil confronts Leland Owlsley.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley is attacked by the [[Masked Man]]]]
Before he could get away, he was confronted by the [[Masked Man]] who pinned him against his car and demanded to know who he worked for, promising that if Owlsley lied, he would hit in the face. When Owlsley tried to insist he worked for [[Silver & Brent]], the man in the mask hit him hard in the face, causing his face to badly bruise. The man in the mask revealed he knew Owlsley worked for [[Wilson Fisk]], but before he could learn anymore about Fisk's activities, he appeared distracted by a [[Stick|sound]] in the distance, Owlsley took the chance and hit him in the neck with a taser, stunning his attacker who fell to the floor before getting in his car and escaping.{{Ref|DD107}}

====Taking Precautions====
[[File:Leland-in-Melvin's-workshop.png|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley taking measurements at the [[Melvin Potter's Workshop|Workshop]]]]
{{Quote|This guy, [[Carl Hoffman|Hoffman]], how much does he know?"<br>"We're taking care of it, Leland."<br>"Well, that fills me with warm comfort. Situation's being handled, all right. Just not by you.|Leland Owlsley and [[Wilson Fisk]]|Shadows in the Glass}}
Due to his recent attack by the [[Masked Man]], Owlsley was taken to [[Melvin Potter]], who fitted him with a kevlar suit for protection. Owlsley and [[Wilson Fisk]] discussed what measures should be put in place to protect him, Fisk suggested that he should be taken to a safe house with armed guards while Owlsley complained bitterly that the recent attacks against them were forcing him to cancel plans to see his [[Lee Owlsley|son]] who had planned to come to [[New York City]] to visit him.
[[File:Leland-Owlsley-Melvin-Potters-Workshop.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley learns of a failed assassination]]
Owlsley reminded Fisk that if the masked man was to throw him off a roof, then a lot of money would be lost along with him. When Fisk asked if this was a threat, Owlsley assured him that he was just stating the obvious. [[James Wesley]] then arrived and informed them that although Detective [[Christian Blake]] had been successfully assassinated by his former partner [[Carl Hoffman]], the man in the mask had gotten into the hospital and got information out of him. Owlsley mocked Fisk for the failure, claiming that situations were becoming more complicated each day.
{{Expand|Owlsley scooping up Hoffman and squirreling him away should be listed here}}
[[File:WHiH - Wilson Fisk Pledges Aid to Hell's Kitchen.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley witnesses [[Wilson Fisk]]'s big speech]]
In an attempt to counteract the condemning exposure Fisk was likely to get as the masked man got closer to learning his identity and his plans, Fisk arranged a press conference with [[WHiH World News]] where he revealed himself to be a private donator of funds to rebuild Hell's Kitchen before anyone could expose his identity. During his speech, Owlsley stood beside Wesley and [[Vanessa Marianna]], with Fisk using his friend Owlsley as an example when he condemned the actions of vigilantes like the masked man, calling Owlsley a pillar of the community.{{Ref|DD108}}

====Poisoning Vanessa Marianna====
[[File:Leland-Owlsley-Suit-Penthouse.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley talks to [[Wilson Fisk]] about his actions]]
{{Quote|[[Madame Gao|Gao]] is right. You've changed."<br>"Change is inevitable... for me... [[New York City|this city]]... and certain relationships."<br>"All right. All right, I'll go speak with her.|[[Wilson Fisk]] and Leland Owlsley|Nelson v. Murdock}}
At [[Wilson Fisk's Penthouse]], Owlsley was informed of [[Nobu Yoshioka]]'s violent [[Duel at Pier 81|death]] while the pair prepared for a fundraiser. Owlsley was mortified by the news, despite Fisk and [[James Wesley]]'s calm reactions. Fisk ordered Owlsley speak to [[Madame Gao]] and convince her that everything was fine in their organization. When Owlsley made a comment about Fisk's relationship with [[Vanessa Marianna]], Fisk spoke to him about what it meant to be in love, seeing the change in Fisk caused by Marianna, Owlsley agreed to speak to Gao.
[[File:Leland-Owlsley-Fisk-Wesley-Alcohol.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley drinking at [[Wilson Fisk]]'s party]]
Owlsley had a meeting with [[Madame Gao]] where they agreed that [[Vanessa Marianna]] was having a negative effect on [[Wilson Fisk]]'s work and they arranged for her to be poisoned at the fundraiser. After Fisk gave his speech, he spoke to Owlsley who assured him that the meeting was a success, Owlsley then offered each of them a glass of poisoned champagne which Marianna gratefully accepted. While Fisk was speaking to a senator, Marianna collapsed along with many other attendants who had also drunk the champagne. Fisk ran to her aid and Owlsley dropped his own glass having not taken a sip yet.{{Ref|DD110}}

====Avoiding Suspicion====
[[File:Leland-Owlsley-Hospital.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley arrives at the [[Metro-General Hospital]]]]
{{Quote|This is awful. Look at [[Wilson Fisk|him]]. How's he gonna run things?"<br>"Not the time, Leland."<br>"This is exactly the time. You keeping score here? You think whoever did this was trying to take [[Vanessa Marianna|Little Miss Hairdo]] out of the equation?|Leland Owlsley and [[James Wesley]]|The Ones We Leave Behind}}
[[Vanessa Marianna]] was rushed to [[Metro-General Hospital]] and Owlsley went along with her and the rest of the group, asking Doctor [[Murray (Doctor)|Murray]] if he also needed to be checked out as he was holding a glass of poisoned champagne; Nurse [[Schwab]] ignored him, however, and continued to focus her attention on Marianna. Owlsley watched as [[Wilson Fisk]] attempted to go with her surgery, but was stopped by the nurse.
[[File:Owlsley-Wesley-Hospital-chat.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley speaking to [[James Wesley]]]]
While Marianna was being treated in the hospital, Owlsley spoke to [[James Wesley]] about how Fisk could run the business in his emotional condition. He claimed that whoever poisoned Marianna was likely after Fisk, not her, so they were in danger and needed proper leadership. When Wesley considered [[Madame Gao]] as a suspect, Owlsley claimed it was more likely the [[Hand]] who were responsible. They were then informed that Marianna was still alive, but three others who drank the champagne were now dead. Wesley then sent Owlsley to speak to Gao for support.
[[File:Leland-Owlsley-James-Wesley-Hospital.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley and [[James Wesley]] discuss the future]]
Owlsley later returned to the hospital and asked about Marianna's condition; Fisk, however, refused to speak to him and returned to her room. Owlsley spoke instead to [[James Wesley]] and claimed Gao had only spoken Chinese and quoted a fortune cookie, but she said she would stand with Fisk. Owlsley recommended that Fisk get back to work, but Wesley told him he would when he was ready, much to Owlsley's annoyance. Owlsley warned that whoever had gone after Fisk would come after him again and would likely succeed in killing him. Wesley simply told him to go home and get some rest.{{Ref|DD111}}

====Keeping the Business Running====
[[File:Leland-Owlsley-speaks-to-Fisk-Wesley-death.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley tries to cheer up [[Wilson Fisk]]]]
{{Quote|It's a shame not everybody'll be there to see it, but... shit happens."<br>"Find out who did this to... to [[Vanessa Marianna|Vanessa]] and to [[James Wesley|Wesley]]."<br>"I'll see what I can shake loose. Just remember, uh... wind blows the hardest the closer you get to the mountaintop.|Leland Owlsley and [[Wilson Fisk]]|The Ones We Leave Behind}}
Owlsley was summoned by [[Wilson Fisk]] to a warehouse. When he arrived, he found Fisk staring at the corpse of [[James Wesley]] who had been shot in the chest. When he asked what had happened, [[Francis]] revealed that Wesley had received a call the night before and had gone out alone with a gun. Hearing this threw Fisk into a rage and he mercilessly beat Francis until Owlsley convinced him to stop. Owlsley discussed who could be responsible, explaining that [[Nobu Yoshioka]]'s accounts were still active and his [[Hand|clan]] were the prime suspects after Yoshioka's death.
[[File:LelandOwlsley-RedLight-S1E12.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley continues worrying about [[Wilson Fisk]]]]
Owlsley had a meeting with Fisk that night where he claimed to have not found any information to blame the [[Hand]] although he still remained suspicious. The desperate Fisk then ordered [[Francis]] to double the reward for information until someone talked. Owlsley questioned if Francis could be trusted after the beating, but Fisk assured him that he could as Wesley had trusted him. Fisk then received a call on [[James Wesley]]'s phone and immediately left the meeting, leaving Owsley both annoyed and concerned over Fisk's mental state due to Wesley's sudden murder.
[[File:Leland-Owlsley-Madame-Gao.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley has his meeting with [[Madame Gao]]]]
Owlsley called a meeting with [[Madame Gao]], who arrived late. She spoke English to him for the first time and claimed to have been detained by unfortunate events involving the [[Devil of Hell's Kitchen]], who had raided and burned down her heroin warehouse. They discussed the risks of [[Wilson Fisk]] learning that they planned to assassinate [[Vanessa Marianna]]. He asked if she was responsible for [[James Wesley]]'s death but she assured him she was not. She told him she was going to her homeland, which was much further away than China, and they would not speak again.{{Ref|DD112}}

====Betrayal Revealed====
[[File:Leland-Owlsley-threatens-Wilson-Fisk.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley starts to threaten [[Wilson Fisk]]]]
{{Quote|My [[Lee Owlsley|son]] and I will be just another transaction, disappearing into the tax-exempt ether. But I'm a fair sort. That's why I'm only taking half your money. You go your way, I go mine. Not what I'd call win-win... but it's as close as we're gonna get with this.|Leland Owlsley to [[Wilson Fisk]]|Daredevil (episode)}}
Upon being called for a meeting with [[Wilson Fisk]] to discuss the final stages of his plans for [[New York City]], Owlsley explained that all was in place except for a replacement for [[Madame Gao]]'s heroin trade. Fisk asked about some irregularities in the transactions. Owlsley claimed it was all perfectly normal as money was being moved around all the time. When he tried to hand the paperwork back, Fisk noted that his hands were shaking and he was shedding sweat. Seeing no other alternative, Owlsley confessed that he and Gao had tried to kill [[Vanessa Marianna]] although he denied any involvement with [[James Wesley]]'s death.
[[File:Leland-Owlsley-death.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Owlsley is killed by [[Wilson Fisk]]]]
Owlsley calmly informed Fisk that their partnership was at an end and Fisk was to hand over half his assets to him. When Fisk asked why he should do this, Owlsley informed him that he had [[Carl Hoffman]] and Hoffman was willing to go to the police if anything happened to him. This threw Fisk into a rage and he refused the offer and hit Owlsley hard across the face. Owlsley attempted to defend himself by striking Fisk on the neck with his taser, but Fisk was so angry it seemed to only fuel his rage. Fisk threw Owlsley down an elevator shaft to his death, where he split his skull upon impact.{{Ref|DD113}}

===Legacy===
====Hoffman's Testimony====
{{Quote|Still got eight minutes. Owlsley don't call by then, we can get out of this dump.|Owlsley's Henchman|Daredevil (episode)}}
Once Owlsley was dead, [[Wilson Fisk]] ordered his contacts within the [[New York City Police Department]] to search through [[New York City]] and find where Owlsley hid [[Carl Hoffman]]. Meanwhile, Owlsley's men noticed he did not check in for 24 hours and prepared to move Hoffman from the hideout and turn him in to the [[FBI]]. However, [[Corbin]] and his officers raided the hideout and gunned down all of Owlsley's men, but before they could kill Hoffman, he was rescued by the [[Daredevil|man in the mask]]. The vigilante had Hoffman to turn himself in to [[Brett Mahoney]], as [[Nelson and Murdock]] organized his testimony, which allowed the FBI and the NYPD to disrupt Fisk's criminal network.{{Ref|DD113}}

==Abilities==
<!-- The power list and levels has been carefully reviewed and approved by Wiki-Projects with the media released as of the end of 2023. DO NOT MAKE arbitrary changes to them or it may lead to blocks. -->
{{Quote|Even if they are, it doesn't mean that Owlsley's using [[Silver & Brent|company]] funds to stash [[Carl Hoffman|Hoffman]]."<br>"Owlsley's a man of financial privilege. I never met one that used his own money when he could use someone else's.|[[Foggy Nelson]] and [[Matt Murdock]]|Daredevil (episode)}}
*'''Master Businessperson''': Owlsley was in charge of finances for [[Wilson Fisk]]'s operation and was highly revered and successful businessman at Wall Street. He was able to launder money in such a way that it became nearly impossible to track, which made him a very valuable asset to Fisk. When Owlsley thought Fisk was getting distracted, Owlsley made a plan to use [[Carl Hoffman]] to scare Fisk into giving Owlsley half of his assets.
{{Quote|Whatever war you're thinking about starting, don't lose sight of the endgame.|Leland Owlsley to [[Wilson Fisk]]|The Ones We Leave Behind}}
*'''Master Tactician''': Never fully trusting [[Wilson Fisk]], Owlsley had backup plans. Realizing that Fisk cared about [[Vanessa Marianna]], he tried to poison her, which eventually led to Owlsley's death when Fisk found out. Owlsley also dealt with issues regarding [[Madame Gao]] and also had to hide [[Carl Hoffman]] from Fisk as Hoffman could testify against him.

==Equipment==
===Weapons===
{{Quote|An old guy just lit you up.|[[Stick]] to [[Matt Murdock]]|Stick (episode)}}
*'''Taser''': Owlsley used a taser he carried around on the [[Daredevil|man in the mask]] and then [[Wilson Fisk]], only for the latter to fight its effects and become enraged.

===Other Equipment===
{{Quote|What's this coated with?"<br>"Polyethylene, glycol, silicate.|Leland Owlsley and [[Melvin Potter]]|Shadows in the Glass}}
*'''Armored Suit''': [[Melvin Potter]] provided Owlsley with a protective suit.

