==Trivia==
*In the comics, Leland Owlsley was a crooked investor and a gangster, who used his resources to fight [[Daredevil]]. He purchased an experimental serum that gave him the ability to fly and transformed his appearance to more bird-like, so he became known as '''The Owl'''.
**In ''[[Shadows in the Glass]]'', [[Melvin Potter]] provided Owlsley with a green protective armor, which was the reference to the Owl's green cloak from the comics.
*Owlsley's plot to murder [[Vanessa Marianna]] is based on the plot the [[Kingpin]]'s associate Lynch used in the comics, where it was believed that Marianna's presence was only distracting Fisk from his criminal activities.
*Owlsley was a 46" long.{{Ref|DD108}}

==Behind the Scenes==
*Leland Owlsley's death scene was originally much different, where he fled [[New York City]] and got onto a boat before he was suddenly assassinated by [[Punisher]] in a [[List of Post-credits Scenes|post-credits scene]]. However, the idea was forced to be dropped as [[Netflix]] at the time was not designed to accomodate post-credits scenes, since the timer to begin the next episode would start as soon as the credits began to play. As a result, Owlsley's death was rewritten to have him be [[Murder of Leland Owlsley|killed]] by [[Wilson Fisk]] instead.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20240529091607/https://www.hypable.com/punisher-daredevil-season-one/ Exclusive: ‘Daredevil’ season 1 coda almost introduced Punisher, says showrunner]</ref>
*Owlsley was originally portrayed by [[Peter Gerety]], but after the actor injured his knee, Gunton was cast to replace him. Gerety's character was then renamed to [[Sammy Silke]].<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2J0Jr_OmDg8 A Conversation with Daredevil Showrunners Erik Oleson and Steven DeKnight]</ref>
*[[David Shumbris]] was a stunt double for [[Bob Gunton]] in the role of Leland Owlsley.

